WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.196 --> 00:00:03.808
Earth

2
00:00:05.234 --> 00:00:05.861
Fire

3
00:00:08.562 --> 00:00:09.461
Air

4
00:00:11.645 --> 00:00:13.213
Water

5
00:00:16.279 --> 00:00:19.331
When I was a boy. my father. Avatar Aang.

6
00:00:19.331 --> 00:00:24.309
 told me a story of how he and his friends
heroically ended the Hundred Years War.

7
00:00:25.173 --> 00:00:27.954
Avatar Aang and Fire Lord Zuko

8
00:00:27.954 --> 00:00:30.130
transformed the Fire Nation colonies

9
00:00:30.130 --> 00:00:31.974
into the United Republic of Nations.

10
00:00:31.974 --> 00:00:36.700
a society where benders and nonbenders 
from all over the world

11
00:00:36.700 --> 00:00:40.824
could live and thrive together in peace and harmony.

12
00:00:40.824 --> 00:00:45.098
They named the capital of this great land Republic City.

13
00:00:46.826 --> 00:00:50.928
Avatar Aang accomplished many remarkable things in his life

14
00:00:50.928 --> 00:00:51.928
but. sadly. his time in this world came to an end.

15
00:00:54.563 --> 00:00:56.750
And like the cycle of the seasons.

16
00:00:56.750 --> 00:01:00.345
the cycle of the Avatar began anew.

17
00:01:14.829 --> 00:01:19.493
"And in the final round the Buzzard Wasps
won with a decisive knockout."

18
00:01:19.493 --> 00:01:21.572
What do you say we go to the arena tonight?

19
00:01:21.572 --> 00:01:23.111
Catch a few Pro-Bending matches?

20
00:01:23.111 --> 00:01:27.226
That sport is a mockery of the
noble tradition of bending.

21
00:01:27.226 --> 00:01:29.111
Come on Tenzin!

22
00:01:29.111 --> 00:01:31.581
I dreamed about seeing a
Pro-Bending match since I was a kid

23
00:01:31.581 --> 00:01:33.680
and now I'm just a ferry ride
away from the arena.

24
00:01:33.680 --> 00:01:35.871
Korra. you're not here to watch that drivel.

25
00:01:35.871 --> 00:01:37.899
You're here to finish your Avatar training.

26
00:01:37.899 --> 00:01:41.284
so for the time being
I want you to remain on the island.

27
00:01:41.284 --> 00:01:43.285
Is that why you're keeping the 
White Lotus sentries around

28
00:01:43.285 --> 00:01:45.515
to watch my every move?

29
00:01:45.515 --> 00:01:47.107
Yes. In order to learn Airbending

30
00:01:47.107 --> 00:01:49.681
I believe you require a
calm. quiet environment

31
00:01:49.681 --> 00:01:51.637
free from any distractions.

32
00:01:51.637 --> 00:01:52.930
Alright.

33
00:01:52.930 --> 00:01:54.209
You're the master.

34
00:02:02.006 --> 00:02:03.041
So

35
00:02:03.041 --> 00:02:06.520
my mother informed me you've
never been able to Airbend before.

36
00:02:08.056 --> 00:02:10.050
Yeah but I don't know why.

37
00:02:10.050 --> 00:02:12.120
The other elements came SO easily to me

38
00:02:12.120 --> 00:02:14.719
but every single time I've tried Airbending

39
00:02:15.341 --> 00:02:16.475
nothing.

40
00:02:16.475 --> 00:02:19.202
That's perfectly all right.
We just need to be patient.

41
00:02:19.202 --> 00:02:20.202
Often the element that's most
difficult for the Avatar to master

42
00:02:22.855 --> 00:02:25.150
 is the one most opposite 
to the Avatar's personality.

43
00:02:25.199 --> 00:02:27.220
For Aang it was Earthbending.

44
00:02:27.220 --> 00:02:30.512
Yeah well. I'm about as opposite 
an Airbender as you can get.

45
00:02:30.916 --> 00:02:32.869
 Let's begin your first lesson.

46
00:02:34.583 --> 00:02:38.320
Korra's gonna Airbend!
Korra's gonna Airbend!

47
00:02:38.320 --> 00:02:40.225
What is that contraption.

48
00:02:40.225 --> 00:02:42.004
A time-honored tool

49
00:02:42.004 --> 00:02:44.894
that teaches the most
fundamental aspect of Airbending.

50
00:02:44.894 --> 00:02:47.431
Jinora would you like
to explain this exercise.

51
00:02:47.443 --> 00:02:49.895
The goal is to weave your
way through the gates

52
00:02:49.895 --> 00:02:51.875
and make it to the other side
without touching them.

53
00:02:53.032 --> 00:02:54.008
Seems easy enough.

54
00:02:54.335 --> 00:02:56.943
Jinora forgot to say you have to make 
it through while the gates are spinning.

55
00:03:06.140 --> 00:03:09.340
The key is to be like the leaf.

56
00:03:10.871 --> 00:03:12.849
Flow

57
00:03:12.849 --> 00:03:14.420
with the movement of the gates.

58
00:03:15.347 --> 00:03:17.714
Jinora will demonstrate.

59
00:03:19.779 --> 00:03:22.393
Airbending is all about spiral movements.

60
00:03:22.393 --> 00:03:23.925
When you meet resistance

61
00:03:23.925 --> 00:03:27.216
you must be able to switch direction
at a moment's notice.

62
00:03:34.763 --> 00:03:35.992
Let's do this.

63
00:03:52.789 --> 00:03:54.517
Don't force your way through!

64
00:03:54.517 --> 00:03:57.389
Dance! Dance like the wind!

65
00:03:57.389 --> 00:04:00.181
Be the leaf!

66
00:04:11.851 --> 00:04:12.967
Airbend!

67
00:04:15.731 --> 00:04:17.393
What is wrong with me?

68
00:04:17.393 --> 00:04:19.222
Airbend!

69
00:04:25.881 --> 00:04:28.615
Maybe I'm just not cut out to be an Airbender.
huh. Naga?

70
00:04:28.615 --> 00:04:30.860
Ladies and gentlemen! I'm coming to you live

71
00:04:30.860 --> 00:04:33.078
from Republic City's Pro-Bending arena

72
00:04:33.078 --> 00:04:35.084
where tonight the best in the world

73
00:04:35.084 --> 00:04:39.017
continue their quest for a spot in 
the upcoming championship tournament. 

74
00:04:39.017 --> 00:04:41.160
Grab your snacks and grab your kids

75
00:04:41.160 --> 00:04:44.108
because this next match is gonna be a doozy!

76
00:04:44.108 --> 00:04:46.413
This Mako's got moxy!

77
00:04:46.413 --> 00:04:48.462
He fires to quick shots.

78
00:04:48.462 --> 00:04:50.772
Yomo is hammered back to zone 3.

79
00:04:50.772 --> 00:04:53.008
Clock is winding down. can Yomo hold on?

80
00:04:53.008 --> 00:04:54.712
He's teetering on the edge of the ring now.

81
00:04:54.712 --> 00:04:57.965
The Fire Ferrets—

82
00:05:00.218 --> 00:05:01.215
Korra come down here. please.

83
00:05:04.504 --> 00:05:05.922
You shut it off at the best part!

84
00:05:05.922 --> 00:05:07.884
I thought I made myself clear.

85
00:05:07.884 --> 00:05:11.181
I don't want you listening to this 
distracting nonsense

86
00:05:11.181 --> 00:05:12.767
But it's their radio.

87
00:05:12.767 --> 00:05:17.851
And technically you said I couldn't watch a match.
You said nothing about listening to one.

88
00:05:17.851 --> 00:05:18.764
You---

89
00:05:18.764 --> 00:05:20.630
you know what I meant.

90
00:05:20.630 --> 00:05:22.072
Anyway shouldn't you—

91
00:05:22.072 --> 00:05:23.072
shouldn't you be in bed by now!

92
00:05:41.528 --> 00:05:43.848
I think I'm doing it wrong.

93
00:05:43.848 --> 00:05:45.328
There's nothing to do.

94
00:05:45.328 --> 00:05:47.813
Let your mind and your spirit be free

95
00:05:47.813 --> 00:05:50.055
for Air is the element of freedom.

96
00:05:52.685 --> 00:05:54.486
Is something funny?

97
00:05:54.486 --> 00:05:58.751
Yeah. you're telling me to embrace freedom
and yet you won't even let me listen to the radio.

98
00:05:59.140 --> 00:06:01.153
And forget about leaving this island.

99
00:06:01.153 --> 00:06:04.298
Please Korra. Look at Meelo.

100
00:06:04.298 --> 00:06:06.042
He's able to meditate peacefully.

101
00:06:09.100 --> 00:06:10.941
He's able to meditate peacefully.

102
00:06:10.941 --> 00:06:11.698
What?

103
00:06:11.698 --> 00:06:14.658
Well. at least he has the relaxing part down.

104
00:06:14.658 --> 00:06:15.721
Whatever.

105
00:06:15.721 --> 00:06:17.944
none of this Airbending stuff
makes any sense to me.

106
00:06:17.944 --> 00:06:19.441
I know you're frustrated

107
00:06:19.441 --> 00:06:21.760
but these teachings will sink in over time

108
00:06:21.760 --> 00:06:23.149
then one day

109
00:06:23.149 --> 00:06:24.911
they'll just click.

110
00:06:26.843 --> 00:06:29.946
Yeah it's not sinking in.

111
00:06:29.946 --> 00:06:31.924
I'm gonna go get a
glass of leechee juice.

112
00:06:31.924 --> 00:06:32.932
Korra!

113
00:06:33.441 --> 00:06:34.421
The meditation's not over yet!

114
00:06:34.421 --> 00:06:36.964
Daddy can I have 
some leechee juice too?

115
00:06:36.964 --> 00:06:38.163
No.

116
00:07:45.978 --> 00:07:47.020
Hey!

117
00:07:47.020 --> 00:07:48.715
What are you doing in my gym?

118
00:07:48.715 --> 00:07:51.736
I was just looking for a bathroom
and I got lost.

119
00:07:51.736 --> 00:07:54.671
Oh the old "I had to pee excuse".

120
00:07:54.671 --> 00:07:57.908
You know. I'm sick and tired of
you kids sneaking in without paying.

121
00:07:57.908 --> 00:07:59.263
I'm taking you to security.

122
00:07:59.263 --> 00:08:01.169
- No wait--!
- There you are!

123
00:08:01.169 --> 00:08:03.244
I've been looking everywhere for you.

124
00:08:03.244 --> 00:08:06.360
It's alright Toza. she's with me.

125
00:08:06.360 --> 00:08:07.497
Yeah. I'm with him.

126
00:08:07.497 --> 00:08:08.497
So you see. we're together.

127
00:08:09.038 --> 00:08:10.435
Well not "together together".

128
00:08:10.435 --> 00:08:13.475
more like friends.
- Right friends. no. no I didn't mean to imply…

129
00:08:13.475 --> 00:08:14.475
Oh you implied it.

130
00:08:14.486 --> 00:08:16.174
I don't care what you are!

131
00:08:16.174 --> 00:08:17.243
I've got work to do.

132
00:08:18.977 --> 00:08:21.255
Right this way miss.

133
00:08:21.255 --> 00:08:23.135
Why thank you sir.

134
00:08:23.553 --> 00:08:25.219
Seriously thanks.

135
00:08:27.260 --> 00:08:28.918
What do you think?

136
00:08:29.523 --> 00:08:31.046
Best seats in the house. huh?

137
00:08:31.046 --> 00:08:32.599
Whoa…

138
00:08:32.599 --> 00:08:34.574
Unbelievable!

139
00:08:34.574 --> 00:08:37.971
this place is even more amazing
than I imagined.

140
00:08:37.971 --> 00:08:39.756
Name's Bolin. by the way.

141
00:08:39.756 --> 00:08:41.045
Korra

142
00:08:41.045 --> 00:08:43.967
- Pssst. Bolin!
- Yeah?

143
00:08:43.967 --> 00:08:48.420
I told you. you have to stop bringing
your crazy fangirls in here before the matches.

144
00:08:48.420 --> 00:08:50.056
Get her out of here.

145
00:08:50.056 --> 00:08:52.363
Ah come on Mako!

146
00:08:52.363 --> 00:08:55.430
I kinda promised her she could stay

147
00:08:55.430 --> 00:08:58.425
but man I got a good feeling.
There's something special about her

148
00:08:58.425 --> 00:09:01.629
I know it. Come here. I want you
to meet my brother

149
00:09:01.629 --> 00:09:03.196
Mako

150
00:09:03.196 --> 00:09:04.196
Mako?

151
00:09:04.488 --> 00:09:05.488
Wow I heard you play on the radio.

152
00:09:06.206 --> 00:09:07.541
Come on Bolin we're up.

153
00:09:07.541 --> 00:09:10.278
Or I could meet him later.

154
00:09:10.278 --> 00:09:11.679
Yeah. Sorry about that.

155
00:09:11.679 --> 00:09:14.550
My brother gets real focused before a match.

156
00:09:14.550 --> 00:09:16.731
Well I gotta go.

157
00:09:16.731 --> 00:09:18.214
Wish me luck.

158
00:09:18.214 --> 00:09:19.738
Not that I'll need it.

159
00:09:19.738 --> 00:09:21.757
Good luck!

160
00:09:21.757 --> 00:09:23.263
Knock 'em out!

161
00:09:28.984 --> 00:09:33.409
Introducing the Fire Ferrets!

162
00:09:33.651 --> 00:09:35.821
Ahhhh!! I love you Bolin.

163
00:09:35.821 --> 00:09:38.458
The rookie Ferrets came out of nowhere

164
00:09:38.458 --> 00:09:41.012
and have made it further
than anyone expected this season.

165
00:09:41.012 --> 00:09:44.019
But tonight they face 
their toughest test yet folks.

166
00:09:47.337 --> 00:09:48.215
And they're off.

167
00:09:49.643 --> 00:09:50.890
The two teams waste no time

168
00:09:50.890 --> 00:09:53.210
trying to blast each other out of zone 1.

169
00:09:55.075 --> 00:09:57.569
Hasook is the first to feel
the heat of the Tigerdilloes.

170
00:09:57.569 --> 00:10:00.724
he tries to return the favor
but they're too fast for him.

171
00:10:00.724 --> 00:10:03.858
While Mako showcases his trademark
cool under fire style.

172
00:10:07.708 --> 00:10:10.970
And the Tigerdilloes score
with a walloping one-two combo.

173
00:10:10.970 --> 00:10:15.007
Can their teammate…

174
00:10:18.484 --> 00:10:19.552
Guess not. 

175
00:10:19.552 --> 00:10:20.841
Mako's over the line. 

176
00:10:20.841 --> 00:10:24.270
The Tigerdilloes get the green line
and advance into Ferret territory.

177
00:10:24.270 --> 00:10:25.661
Come on. Ferrets!

178
00:10:29.556 --> 00:10:31.068
Look's like Hasook's in trouble.

179
00:10:31.068 --> 00:10:33.355
He's in zone 3 teetering over the drink. 

180
00:10:36.403 --> 00:10:37.944
And Hasook takes a dip.

181
00:10:37.944 --> 00:10:39.675
He'll be back for round two.

182
00:10:39.675 --> 00:10:42.704
Assuming the fabulous bending brothers
can hold their ground until he next round.

183
00:10:45.636 --> 00:10:51.052
Round 1 goes to the
Golden Temple Tigerdilloes!

184
00:10:51.052 --> 00:10:53.677
Come on. Hasook
get your act together!

185
00:10:58.116 --> 00:11:02.170
The Fire Ferrets are knocked into zone 2
and the Tigerdilloes advance.

186
00:11:19.284 --> 00:11:22.515
The Fire Ferrets sinch the round
in the closing seconds.

187
00:11:22.515 --> 00:11:27.541
That's one a piece. Still anyone's match
as we go into the third and final round.

188
00:11:29.177 --> 00:11:30.784
Hasook stumbles

189
00:11:30.784 --> 00:11:33.645
and now he tumbles right into his teammate.

190
00:11:33.645 --> 00:11:36.475
He and Bolin better untangle quick
if they don't want to—

191
00:11:36.475 --> 00:11:38.017
Oh too late!

192
00:11:38.915 --> 00:11:40.021
Oh no!

193
00:11:40.021 --> 00:11:42.091
It's all up to Mako now.

194
00:11:43.653 --> 00:11:45.010
he's bobbing and weaving.

195
00:11:45.010 --> 00:11:46.651
but he's not hitting back!

196
00:11:46.651 --> 00:11:49.938
If he's knocked out
the Ferrets' fabulous season is over.

197
00:11:51.425 --> 00:11:53.219
He is dancing on the edge of the ring

198
00:11:53.219 --> 00:11:55.139
withstanding the three on one barrage.

199
00:11:55.139 --> 00:11:58.604
It seems his plan is to let the Tigerdilloes
punch themselves out.

200
00:11:58.604 --> 00:12:00.348
And his plan is working.

201
00:12:00.348 --> 00:12:01.805
Han is in the pool!

202
00:12:01.805 --> 00:12:05.162
They've got nothing left in the tank
and Mako's on the offensive!

203
00:12:06.207 --> 00:12:08.107
It's two on one.

204
00:12:08.284 --> 00:12:09.771
scratch that it's one on one.

205
00:12:09.771 --> 00:12:12.404
And it's an Earth and Fire slugfest!

206
00:12:12.404 --> 00:12:17.763
There's so much smoke and dust
I can't even see where the Fire Ferret is. 

207
00:12:21.175 --> 00:12:23.110
It's a knock out!

208
00:12:23.110 --> 00:12:25.616
What a win they had a hat trick folks!

209
00:12:25.616 --> 00:12:30.428
Mako pulls off the upset of the season
winning the match for the Fire Ferrets!

210
00:12:39.466 --> 00:12:40.168
Yes!

211
00:12:40.168 --> 00:12:43.450
One more win and we're in
the championship tournament!

212
00:12:44.895 --> 00:12:47.420
So. what'd ya think Korra?

213
00:12:47.420 --> 00:12:49.499
Bolin's got some moves. huh?

214
00:12:49.499 --> 00:12:50.871
What did I think?

215
00:12:50.871 --> 00:12:51.979
What did I think?

216
00:12:52.136 --> 00:12:53.631
That was amazing!

217
00:12:53.631 --> 00:12:55.827
You did more harm than good out there.

218
00:12:55.827 --> 00:12:57.342
You almost cost us the match.

219
00:12:57.342 --> 00:12:58.835
We won didn't we?

220
00:12:58.835 --> 00:13:00.717
- Barely
- Get off my case pal.

221
00:13:02.759 --> 00:13:03.705
Useless.

222
00:13:03.705 --> 00:13:05.764
You guys were incredible out there.

223
00:13:05.764 --> 00:13:08.247
Especially you Mr. Hatrick.

224
00:13:08.247 --> 00:13:09.798
Oh you're still here…

225
00:13:09.798 --> 00:13:11.240
Oh you're still a jerk…

226
00:13:13.335 --> 00:13:14.152
anyway.

227
00:13:14.152 --> 00:13:16.180
I've been immersed in bending my whole life

228
00:13:16.180 --> 00:13:18.088
but I never learned to move like that.

229
00:13:18.088 --> 00:13:20.180
It's like there's a whole new style here.

230
00:13:20.180 --> 00:13:22.098
Think you could show me a few tricks?

231
00:13:22.098 --> 00:13:24.303
Absolutely!

232
00:13:24.303 --> 00:13:25.417
Right now?

233
00:13:25.417 --> 00:13:27.139
Come on Bolin.

234
00:13:27.139 --> 00:13:28.336
Just ignore him.

235
00:13:28.336 --> 00:13:30.567
Yeah I could show you the basics.

236
00:13:30.771 --> 00:13:33.930
I'm just not sure how my Earthbending
would translate to your Waterbending

237
00:13:34.318 --> 00:13:36.062
but we'll figure it out.

238
00:13:36.062 --> 00:13:38.117
Won't be a problem.
I'm actually an Earthbender.

239
00:13:38.117 --> 00:13:41.106
I'm sorry! No. no 
I didn't mean to assume—

240
00:13:41.106 --> 00:13:44.373
I was just figuring.
with your Water Tribe get up

241
00:13:44.373 --> 00:13:47.447
that you are a Water Tribe gal.

242
00:13:47.447 --> 00:13:49.981
No you're right.
I'm a Waterbender

243
00:13:49.981 --> 00:13:52.267
and a Firebender.

244
00:13:53.476 --> 00:13:54.768
Hmm…hhmm.
I'm very confused right now.

245
00:13:54.768 --> 00:13:57.250
You're the Avatar

246
00:13:57.250 --> 00:13:58.770
and I'm an idiot.

247
00:13:58.770 --> 00:14:00.290
Both are true.

248
00:14:03.570 --> 00:14:05.173
No way… The Avatar!

249
00:14:06.117 --> 00:14:07.991
Alright. Let's see what you got.

250
00:14:12.146 --> 00:14:13.633
That was great!

251
00:14:13.633 --> 00:14:14.780
Good power!

252
00:14:14.780 --> 00:14:18.066
But in a real match you'd be a sitting turtleduck.

253
00:14:18.066 --> 00:14:19.891
Not so upright and flatfooted.

254
00:14:19.891 --> 00:14:22.446
Stay light on your toes up until the moment

255
00:14:22.446 --> 00:14:24.631
when you need to dig in and strike.

256
00:14:24.631 --> 00:14:26.628
Then—

257
00:14:29.077 --> 00:14:31.362
Okay. let me try it again.

258
00:14:35.827 --> 00:14:38.449
Wow! Nice adjustment.

259
00:14:38.449 --> 00:14:40.185
You're a natural at this!

260
00:14:40.185 --> 00:14:41.542
- Not bad.
- What's it take

261
00:14:42.142 --> 00:14:43.291
to impress this guy?

262
00:14:43.291 --> 00:14:45.372
What? I said not bad.

263
00:14:46.484 --> 00:14:48.687
You know what. it's getting late.

264
00:14:48.687 --> 00:14:51.429
I think I'm gonna turn in.
You kids have fun.

265
00:14:51.429 --> 00:14:53.886
Nice to meet you. Avatar Korra.

266
00:14:53.886 --> 00:14:56.721
Yeah. real pleasure.

267
00:14:56.721 --> 00:14:58.984
See you upstairs bro.

268
00:14:58.984 --> 00:15:00.051
Upstairs? You guys live here?

269
00:15:00.051 --> 00:15:01.739
Yeah. in the attic.

270
00:15:01.739 --> 00:15:02.981
It's nothing fancy

271
00:15:02.981 --> 00:15:04.276
but we have great views.

272
00:15:04.276 --> 00:15:06.288
But back to bending.

273
00:15:06.816 --> 00:15:08.336
Why don't you throw
that combination one more time.

274
00:15:19.446 --> 00:15:21.337
Patience Korra!

275
00:15:34.290 --> 00:15:38.459
That was a 2000-year-old historical treasure…

276
00:15:38.459 --> 00:15:40.267
what…

277
00:15:40.267 --> 00:15:41.728
what is wrong with you?!

278
00:15:41.728 --> 00:15:43.122
There's nothing wrong with me!

279
00:15:43.122 --> 00:15:45.445
I've been practicing just like you taught me!

280
00:15:45.445 --> 00:15:47.469
But it isn't sinking in okay!

281
00:15:47.469 --> 00:15:49.559
It hasn't clicked like you said it would!

282
00:15:49.559 --> 00:15:51.916
Korra this isn't something you can force.

283
00:15:51.916 --> 00:15:53.741
If you would only listen to me…

284
00:15:53.741 --> 00:15:56.067
I have been!
But you know what I think?

285
00:15:56.067 --> 00:15:57.161
Maybe the problem isn't me.

286
00:15:57.161 --> 00:15:59.371
maybe the reason
I haven't learned Airbending yet

287
00:15:59.371 --> 00:16:01.576
is because you're a terrible teacher.

288
00:16:03.984 --> 00:16:06.075
Yeah you're a terrible teacher. Daddy!

289
00:16:19.069 --> 00:16:20.743
Okay!

290
00:16:20.743 --> 00:16:21.831
Everyone here?

291
00:16:21.831 --> 00:16:22.935
Wait…

292
00:16:22.935 --> 00:16:24.365
where's Korra?

293
00:16:24.365 --> 00:16:26.881
Honestly Pema.
I am at my wit's end with that girl.

294
00:16:26.881 --> 00:16:28.756
I don't know how to get through to her.

295
00:16:28.756 --> 00:16:33.413
The best thing you can do right now

296
00:16:33.413 --> 00:16:35.360
is give Korra some space.

297
00:16:35.360 --> 00:16:38.651
You must promise me that
your teenage years won't be like this.

298
00:16:38.651 --> 00:16:42.130
I will make no such promises.

299
00:16:48.758 --> 00:16:51.291
I didn't miss your match did I?

300
00:16:51.291 --> 00:16:53.098
You guys look like you lost already.

301
00:16:53.098 --> 00:16:55.908
- We might as well have.
- Hasook's a no good no show.

302
00:16:56.935 --> 00:16:59.156
You got two minutes
to come out ready to play

303
00:16:59.156 --> 00:17:00.810
or you're disqualified.

304
00:17:00.810 --> 00:17:03.250
Well there goes our shot
at the tournament

305
00:17:03.250 --> 00:17:05.183
and the winnings.

306
00:17:05.183 --> 00:17:06.941
Couldn't you ask one of those guys to fill in?

307
00:17:06.941 --> 00:17:09.970
Nah. the rules say you can only compete on one team.

308
00:17:09.970 --> 00:17:12.656
Well then…what about me?

309
00:17:12.656 --> 00:17:14.376
I'm a topnotch Waterbender

310
00:17:14.376 --> 00:17:15.813
if I do say so myself.

311
00:17:15.813 --> 00:17:17.759
But you're the Avatar…

312
00:17:17.759 --> 00:17:19.121
isn't that cheating?

313
00:17:19.121 --> 00:17:21.000
It isn't cheating if
I only do Waterbending.

314
00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:22.824
No way.
I'd rather forfeit

315
00:17:22.824 --> 00:17:24.336
than look like a fool out there.

316
00:17:24.462 --> 00:17:25.094
Wow

317
00:17:25.094 --> 00:17:27.229
thanks for the vote of confidence…

318
00:17:27.229 --> 00:17:28.693
 Time's up
you in or out?

319
00:17:28.693 --> 00:17:29.490
- We're in.
- We are?

320
00:17:29.490 --> 00:17:31.577
- Yes!
- Hey. I didn't agree to this!

321
00:17:33.087 --> 00:17:33.087
You can thank me later.

322
00:17:33.087 --> 00:17:34.879
This girl is crazy…

323
00:17:34.879 --> 00:17:36.444
Looks like the Fire Ferrets

324
00:17:36.444 --> 00:17:39.717
have ferreted out a
last minute replacement Waterbender.

325
00:17:39.717 --> 00:17:41.359
Let's see if she's another
diamond in the rough

326
00:17:41.359 --> 00:17:43.059
like the brothers
from the school of hard knocks.

327
00:17:44.235 --> 00:17:46.691
Don't do anything too fancy
or aggressive.

328
00:17:46.691 --> 00:17:48.352
In fact. don't do anything.

329
00:17:48.352 --> 00:17:50.441
Just try not to get knocked
off the ring.

330
00:17:50.441 --> 00:17:52.075
You got it captain.

331
00:17:53.676 --> 00:17:54.786
Players

332
00:17:54.786 --> 00:17:55.981
are you ready?

333
00:18:02.996 --> 00:18:04.850
Whoo! Man overboard!

334
00:18:05.907 --> 00:18:06.970
Fire Ferret Waterbender penalty.

335
00:18:07.304 --> 00:18:08.774
move back one zone.

336
00:18:08.774 --> 00:18:10.637
What? Why?

337
00:18:10.637 --> 00:18:13.185
You're only allowed to
knock players off the back of the ring.

338
00:18:13.185 --> 00:18:14.728
not over the sides.

339
00:18:15.677 --> 00:18:17.001
Oh…whoops.

340
00:18:18.608 --> 00:18:20.199
And we're back in action

341
00:18:20.199 --> 00:18:24.198
after that hiccup. But I'm not so sure
this replacement player knows what she's doing.

342
00:18:26.014 --> 00:18:26.961
Fowl! Over the line!

343
00:18:26.961 --> 00:18:28.629
Move back to zone three.

344
00:18:28.629 --> 00:18:31.064
Ugh! I'll show you over the line.

345
00:18:34.175 --> 00:18:37.255
The Platypus Bears take round 1.

346
00:18:38.181 --> 00:18:41.008
The Platypus Bears know a green player
when they see one

347
00:18:41.008 --> 00:18:44.439
and they are focusing the brunt
of their bending on this poor girl.

348
00:18:47.887 --> 00:18:48.986
What a minute.

349
00:18:48.986 --> 00:18:51.055
did that Waterbender just Earthbend?

350
00:18:52.977 --> 00:18:54.544
Fowl!

351
00:18:54.544 --> 00:18:56.067
I think.

352
00:18:58.825 --> 00:19:00.238
Did I see that right?

353
00:19:00.238 --> 00:19:03.955
Hold on folks we're just waiting
for the Referee's official call

354
00:19:03.955 --> 00:19:06.747
but I think this replacement player could be…

355
00:19:06.747 --> 00:19:08.581
Pardon me everyone. has anyone seen Korra this evening?

356
00:19:08.581 --> 00:19:10.053
She's not in her room.

357
00:19:10.053 --> 00:19:11.564
You've gotta be kidding me!

358
00:19:11.564 --> 00:19:13.705
She's the Avatar. folks

359
00:19:13.705 --> 00:19:15.619
playing in a Pro-Bending match!

360
00:19:15.619 --> 00:19:17.264
Can you believe that?

361
00:19:17.264 --> 00:19:18.675
I'll get her myself!

362
00:19:21.222 --> 00:19:23.999
The Avatar will be permitted to continue

363
00:19:23.999 --> 00:19:26.392
so long as she solely bends water.

364
00:19:30.693 --> 00:19:34.081
This girl may be the Avatar but she's no Pro-Bender

365
00:19:34.081 --> 00:19:36.621
and the Platypus Bears are intent
on exploiting that weakness.

366
00:19:36.621 --> 00:19:39.043
They're giving her their best

367
00:19:39.043 --> 00:19:40.879
and her best is not enough to stop it.

368
00:19:41.073 --> 00:19:42.420
Aaaaaannd---

369
00:19:42.420 --> 00:19:43.435
she's in the drink.

370
00:19:50.654 --> 00:19:53.134
Oh hey Tenzin…

371
00:19:53.134 --> 00:19:55.968
I thought you didn't like
coming to these matches.

372
00:19:57.445 --> 00:20:00.116
Once again you have
flagrantly disobeyed my orders.

373
00:20:00.116 --> 00:20:01.877
You were to stay on the island.

374
00:20:01.877 --> 00:20:02.875
Let's go.

375
00:20:02.875 --> 00:20:03.617
No!

376
00:20:03.617 --> 00:20:05.444
I'm kind of in the middle of something.

377
00:20:05.444 --> 00:20:07.521
I have tried my very best to get through to you

378
00:20:07.521 --> 00:20:09.379
by being gentle and patient

379
00:20:09.379 --> 00:20:12.401
But clearly the only thing
you respond to is force.

380
00:20:12.401 --> 00:20:15.364
So I am ordering you to come back to the temple.
Right now!

381
00:20:15.364 --> 00:20:19.821
Why? So I can sit around and meditate about how bad I am at Airbending?

382
00:20:19.821 --> 00:20:23.385
You know I'm beginning to think
there's a reason I haven't been able to learn it.

383
00:20:23.385 --> 00:20:25.544
because maybe I don't even need!

384
00:20:25.544 --> 00:20:26.728
What?

385
00:20:26.728 --> 00:20:28.478
That is a ludicrous suggestion!

386
00:20:28.478 --> 00:20:31.840
The Avatar needs to learn Airbending.
it is not optional!

387
00:20:31.840 --> 00:20:34.386
No. THIS is what I need to learn!

388
00:20:34.386 --> 00:20:36.080
Modern styles of fighting!

389
00:20:36.080 --> 00:20:38.756
Being Avatar isn't all about fighting. Korra!

390
00:20:38.756 --> 00:20:40.657
When will you learn that?

391
00:20:40.657 --> 00:20:42.340
I have a match to go finish.

392
00:20:43.261 --> 00:20:46.981
The Platypus Bears win round 2!

393
00:20:46.831 --> 00:20:49.440
Round 3!

394
00:20:54.156 --> 00:20:58.137
The Platypus Bears come out of the gate
and quickly go after the Ferret brothers.

395
00:20:58.137 --> 00:21:03.170
They're corralled in the corner. wedged in the edge of zone 1
unable to come to the Avatar's rescue

396
00:21:03.170 --> 00:21:05.026
and boy does she need it.

397
00:21:10.755 --> 00:21:14.591
Looks like the Avatar's Pro-Bending
debut is gonna be cut short

398
00:21:14.811 --> 00:21:18.501
as she's pushed back to zone 3
and the water is calling her name.

399
00:21:18.501 --> 00:21:20.761
It's only a matter of time before—

400
00:21:20.761 --> 00:21:24.484
Hold the phone. stop the presses!
She's still in the game folks!

401
00:21:24.484 --> 00:21:26.564
And she's moving like an
entirely different player!

402
00:21:26.564 --> 00:21:30.635
Suddenly all of the Platypus Bear
strikes are only striking air.

403
00:21:32.319 --> 00:21:33.868
Well how about that…

404
00:21:36.156 --> 00:21:38.205
The Platypus Bears have no juice left

405
00:21:38.205 --> 00:21:40.583
but Mako and Bolin are still fresh and juicy.

406
00:22:05.098 --> 00:22:06.005
Knockout!

407
00:22:06.005 --> 00:22:10.651
The Fire Ferrets come from
way behind and steal the win!

408
00:22:10.875 --> 00:22:13.722
What an upset folks!
The rookies. Avatar in tow.

409
00:22:13.722 --> 00:22:16.013
have nabbed a place in
the championship tournament!

410
00:22:16.013 --> 00:22:18.429
I cannot believe it!

411
00:22:23.478 --> 00:22:25.241
Korra. what can I say?

412
00:22:25.241 --> 00:22:28.005
You really came alive in that last round.

413
00:22:28.005 --> 00:22:30.011
The way you dodged their attacks…

414
00:22:30.011 --> 00:22:31.430
you are a natural.

415
00:22:31.430 --> 00:22:32.468
Thanks

416
00:22:32.468 --> 00:22:34.011
but I can't take all the credit.

417
00:22:34.011 --> 00:22:35.927
someone else taught me those moves.

418
00:22:44.055 --> 00:22:45.762
I'm really sorry

419
00:22:45.762 --> 00:22:47.960
about everything I said.

420
00:22:47.960 --> 00:22:50.125
I was really frustrated with myself and

421
00:22:50.125 --> 00:22:51.888
I took it out on you.

422
00:22:51.888 --> 00:22:54.139
I think I owe an apology too.

423
00:22:54.139 --> 00:22:56.471
I was trying to teach you about patience

424
00:22:56.471 --> 00:22:58.173
and I lost mine.

425
00:22:58.173 --> 00:22:59.829
No hard feelings?

426
00:22:59.829 --> 00:23:00.829
Of course not.

427
00:23:00.839 --> 00:23:03.515
By the way you were really
good out there tonight.

428
00:23:03.515 --> 00:23:05.797
You moved like an Airbender.

429
00:23:05.797 --> 00:23:08.218
You stayed and watched?

430
00:23:08.218 --> 00:23:12.256
I did. Pro-Bending turned out to be
the perfect teaching tool for you.

431
00:23:15.877 --> 00:23:18.628
I'll see you tomorrow for
Airbending practice bright and early!

432
00:23:18.628 --> 00:23:22.030
And by the way I kinda
permanently joined the Fire Ferrets

433
00:23:22.030 --> 00:23:23.728
and we're playing in the tournament
in a couple of weeks!
